Converts a generic type `T` into an `Rc<T>`

The conversion allocates on the heap and moves `t`
from the stack into it.

# Example
```rust
# use std::rc::Rc;
let x = 5;
let rc = Rc::new(5);

assert_eq!(Rc::from(x), rc);
```
